pr_review_comment_body:
The json dump should have made booleans without the parenthesis so that the json boolean type is used, i.e.
```
"attrs": {
  "flatten": "True",
  "no_bias": "False",
  "num_hidden": "1000"
}
# should have been
"attrs": {
  "flatten": True,
  "no_bias": False,
  "num_hidden": "1000"
}
```

@piiswrong would it be OK to change json export to properly use json boolean?

@scottpurdy There's not bug longer. The bug arose because I revived code that shoudn't be revived. Darwin always used the same code than Linux which is under `#else` block (https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/blame/master/src/nupic/os/Timer.cpp#L101). It seems that the code under `NTA_PLATFORM_darwin` never was used and this block exists since April/2013:

https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/blame/master/src/nupic/os/Timer.cpp#L69

It's simply a dead code that I shound't have revived.

Seems that we will need to copy over the initialization of m_tmp[I], Only m_args was removed.

for (unsigned i = 0; i < 2; i++) { 
   m_tmp[i] = allocate(m_init_cell_capacity); 
}

